<section class="beliefs">
    <div class="beliefs__container">
        <div class="beliefs__intro">
            <h2 class="beliefs__heading">What We Believe</h2>
            <p class="beliefs__subheading">Our faith is built on the Bible alone</p>
        </div>

        <div class="beliefs__grid">
            <div class="belief-card">
                <div class="belief-card__number">01</div>
                <h3 class="belief-card__title">One God</h3>
                <p class="belief-card__text">
                    We believe in one God, the Father, creator of heaven and earth, as revealed in Scripture.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="belief-card">
                <div class="belief-card__number">02</div>
                <h3 class="belief-card__title">Jesus Christ</h3>
                <p class="belief-card__text">
                    We believe Jesus is the Son of God, our Savior who died for our sins and was raised to life.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="belief-card">
                <div class="belief-card__number">03</div>
                <h3 class="belief-card__title">The Bible</h3>
                <p class="belief-card__text">
                    We believe the Bible is God's inspired word, our sole authority for faith and practice.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="belief-card">
                <div class="belief-card__number">04</div>
                <h3 class="belief-card__title">Kingdom of God</h3>
                <p class="belief-card__text">
                    We believe Jesus will return to establish God's Kingdom on earth, bringing peace and righteousness.
                </p>
            </div>
</div>

        <div class="beliefs__cta">
            <a href="/about" class="beliefs__link">Explore Our Beliefs in Detail →</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="faq">
    <div class="faq__container">
        <div class="faq__content">
            <h2 class="faq__heading">Common Questions</h2>
            
            <div class="faq__list">
                <details class="faq__item" open>
                    <summary class="faq__question">
                        Can everyone attend?
                        <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
                        </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="faq__answer">
                        <p>Yes. We have classes for children and adults, so there is something for individuals of all ages.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq__item">
                    <summary class="faq__question">
                        Will I feel comfortable attending alone?
                        <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
                        </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="faq__answer">
                        <p>Absolutely! We have many members who first visited alone. Our community is welcoming and friendly, and we make it a priority to help newcomers feel at home. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us, and we'll be happy to offer you a guide to make you feel welcome.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq__item">
                    <summary class="faq__question">
                        Will I have to participate?
                        <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
                        </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="faq__answer">
                        <p>Not at all. Visitors are welcome to simply observe and learn. There's no pressure to participate in any way you're not comfortable with. You can sit back, listen, and take everything in at your own pace.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq__item">
                    <summary class="faq__question">
                        What are your services like?
                        <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
                        </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="faq__answer">
                        <p>Our services are simple and focused on Scripture. Sunday morning includes hymns, prayers, Bible readings, and the breaking of bread (for our baptized members) in remembrance of Jesus Christ. Wednesday evenings are interactive Bible studies where we explore God's word together in presented classes by a variety of speakers, offering time for discussion and sharing of ideas.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq__item">
                    <summary class="faq__question">
                        What should I wear?
                        <svg class="faq__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
                        </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="faq__answer">
                        <p>Come as you are! Our members dress formally to Sunday School and Memorial Service, but are welcome to wear casual attire to Wednesday Evening Bible Class.</p>
                    </div>
                </details>
            </div>

            <a href="/contact" class="faq__link">Ask Us a Question</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq__image">
            <img src="/assets/ecclesia.jpeg" alt="Welcoming church member" />
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="bible-unlocked">
    <div class="bible-unlocked__container">
        <h2 class="bible-unlocked__heading">Bible Unlocked</h2>
